<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="555" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1127,308,748]" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,270,308,332]" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body smaller (8.5–12.6 mm), red. Antennomere 1 short, much shorter than antennomere 2 or length of pronotum. Sexual dimorphism indistinct, callar lobe only weakly gibbose in both sexes (
<figureCitation box="[401,529,372,396]" captionStart="Figs 60–63. 60–61" captionStartId="48.[151,188,1540,1559]" captionTargetBox="[211,1066,225,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-10@48.[205,1073,219,1507]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Figs 60–63. 60–61 – Physopelta (Physopeltoides) dentipes sp. nov. 60 – male, paratype; 61 – female, paratype.62–63 – Physopelta (Afrophysopelta) melanoptera Distant, 1904. 62 – male; 63 – female. (Photo: L. Dembický)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5739997" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5739997/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">Figs 62−63</figureCitation>
). Profemora of both sexes not incrassate (
<figureCitation box="[987,1113,372,396]" captionStart="Figs 60–63. 60–61" captionStartId="48.[151,188,1540,1559]" captionTargetBox="[211,1066,225,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-10@48.[205,1073,219,1507]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Figs 60–63. 60–61 – Physopelta (Physopeltoides) dentipes sp. nov. 60 – male, paratype; 61 – female, paratype.62–63 – Physopelta (Afrophysopelta) melanoptera Distant, 1904. 62 – male; 63 – female. (Photo: L. Dembický)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5739997" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5739997/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">Figs 62−63</figureCitation>
), their ventral surface with a longitudinal furrow, provided with a row of small denticles on each sides of the furrow, and two larger teeth anteapically on dorsal surface (
<figureCitation box="[987,1114,436,460]" captionStart="Figs 64–69" captionStartId="56.[150,187,1274,1293]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,220,1256]" captionTargetId="figure-10@56.[151,1128,219,1256]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Figs 64–69. Physopelta (Afrophysopelta) melanoptera Distant, 1904, male. 64 – fore coxae and trochanters (magnification 75×); 65 – detail of procoxa and protrochanter (110×); 66–67 – profemur: 66 – anterior view (35×), 67 – ventral surface (70×); 68 – external scent efferent system (100×); 69 – peritreme and evaporatorium (170×). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (Figs 64, 66–68), 0.5 mm (Figs 65, 69). (SEM micrographs: P. Kment)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740001" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740001/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">Figs 66−67</figureCitation>
). Meso- and metafemora lacking both denticles and longitudinal furrow. Tibiae unarmed in both sexes. Labium surpassing metacoxae. Stridulatory organs on fore leg lacking (
<figureCitation box="[988,1114,500,524]" captionStart="Figs 64–69" captionStartId="56.[150,187,1274,1293]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,220,1256]" captionTargetId="figure-10@56.[151,1128,219,1256]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Figs 64–69. Physopelta (Afrophysopelta) melanoptera Distant, 1904, male. 64 – fore coxae and trochanters (magnification 75×); 65 – detail of procoxa and protrochanter (110×); 66–67 – profemur: 66 – anterior view (35×), 67 – ventral surface (70×); 68 – external scent efferent system (100×); 69 – peritreme and evaporatorium (170×). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (Figs 64, 66–68), 0.5 mm (Figs 65, 69). (SEM micrographs: P. Kment)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740001" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740001/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">Figs 64−65</figureCitation>
). Peritreme of metathoracic scent gland oriented longitudinally, crescent-shaped, projecting both anteriad and posteriad of ostiole (
<figureCitation box="[569,696,564,588]" captionStart="Figs 64–69" captionStartId="56.[150,187,1274,1293]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,220,1256]" captionTargetId="figure-10@56.[151,1128,219,1256]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Figs 64–69. Physopelta (Afrophysopelta) melanoptera Distant, 1904, male. 64 – fore coxae and trochanters (magnification 75×); 65 – detail of procoxa and protrochanter (110×); 66–67 – profemur: 66 – anterior view (35×), 67 – ventral surface (70×); 68 – external scent efferent system (100×); 69 – peritreme and evaporatorium (170×). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (Figs 64, 66–68), 0.5 mm (Figs 65, 69). (SEM micrographs: P. Kment)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740001" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740001/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">Figs 68−69</figureCitation>
). Paramere with apex short and narrow, outer margin basally with small angulate process (
<figureCitation box="[686,812,596,620]" captionStart="Figs 75–79" captionStartId="58.[151,188,594,613]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,220,578]" captionTargetId="figure-367@58.[151,1126,219,578]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="Figs 75–79. Physopelta (Afrophysopelta) melanoptera Distant, 1904, male, paramere (different orientations; 230×). Scale bar: 0.2 mm. (SEM micrographs: P. Kment)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740007" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740007/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">Figs 75−79</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="555" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1127,308,748]" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,628,652]" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is composed by the prefix 
<emphasis box="[683,729,629,652]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">Afro</emphasis>
-, derived from Africa, and the genus name 
<taxonomicName box="[216,334,661,684]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Physopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[216,334,661,684]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">Physopelta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, referring to the area of distribution of the subgenus. Gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="555" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1127,308,748]" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,346,692,716]" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">Species included.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Stehlík, 2013" authorityName="Stehlík" authorityYear="2013" box="[353,515,693,716]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Physopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Afrophysopelta">
<emphasis box="[353,515,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="555">Afrophysopelta</emphasis>
